<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLITICAL NOTE; LOST OPPORTUNITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Joe Scott is a Los Angeles political consultant. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California gubernatorial candidates would have us believe that they would 
love to break clear of the handlers and image-makers and share with the voters 
the authentic nature of their candidacies. 
</P>
<P>
 But I can't help recalling a July invitation from Cardinal Roger Mahony to 
both candidates to participate in a late August forum in Los Angeles. It would 
have been a dialogue, not a debate, to discuss public-policy issues including 
health care, crime, immigration and welfare reform. 
</P>
<P>
 Predictably, Gov. Pete Wilson and Treasurer Kathleen Brown rejected out of 
hand a unique opportunity to engage in serious and substantive discourse on 
pivotal issues. No wonder not only the press but also the public is cynical 
about the current political season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
