<P>
BRIEFLY; MUSIC: BLUES, JAZZ STAMPS TO DEBUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Commemorative stamps honoring jazz and blues greats Billie Holliday, Muddy 
Waters, Bessie Smith and several other well-known artists will be unveiled in a 
ceremony Saturday at a local nightclub. 
</P>
<P>
 The stamps, part of the United States Postal Service Legends of American Music 
series, will be shown at the House of Blues nightclub on Sunset Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 "People the world over will get to know how important these musicians were and 
still are to American music," Los Angeles Postmaster Jesse Durazo said. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will include a concert by several local jazz, blues and gospel 
groups such as the Hollywood Fats Band and Big Jay McNeely. 
