<HEADLINE>
<P>
SECOND TO 'NONE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Now that Labor Day is behind us, the campaigning for the November election 
is in full swing. 
</P>
<P>
 Reading the newspaper and flyers received through the mail and listening to 
the TV news and TV campaign announcements it is great to see that we have only 
one party to vote for: the Democ-Repub Party. 
</P>
<P>
 And in California only one candidate for each of the top post, i.e., Kathleen 
Pete Brown Wilson for governor and Dick Dianne Huffington Feinstein for U.S. 
senator. 
</P>
<P>
 Personally I am going to vote for the new party "None of the above." 
</P>
<P>
 Until we get a party that will listen to the people and not to the special 
interests "None of the above" will always get my vote. 
</P>
<P>
 DAVID E. TEICHMILLER 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 
</P>
</TEXT>
