<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: RANCHO SANTA MARGARITA; MEASURE A OPPONENTS TO HAVE TOWN 
MEETING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rancho Santa Margarita Civic Assn. will have a town meeting tonight to 
discuss how residents can fight a November ballot initiative that asks voter 
approval to build a commercial airport at the El Toro Marine Corps Air Station. 
</P>
<P>
 The 7:30 p.m. meeting will be at Trabuco Mesa School, 21301 Avenida De Las 
Flores. 
</P>
<P>
 The association has joined with other South County residents to form a 
committee to defeat the ballot initiative known as Measure A. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee is called Taxpayers for Responsible Planning. 
</P>
<P>
 The group contends that converting the Marine Corps base to a commercial 
airport would hurt Rancho Santa Margarita and other nearby communities by 
increasing noise and traffic. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 770-4014. 
</P>
