<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; GOLDEN WEST TO OFFER PEPPER SPRAY 
CLASSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golden West College is offering a series of Saturday workshops to train people 
in the use of pepper spray and Mace. Those completing the course and passing a 
test will be given a certificate required by the state to legally carry the 
stinging sprays. 
</P>
<P>
 The course, from 9 a.m. to noon on Sept. 24, Oct. 15 and Nov. 5 in Room 110 of 
the Business Building, will be taught by retired Westminster Police Capt. David 
E. Wiggs. 
</P>
<P>
 "Participants will learn how to properly use pepper spray and Mace," said 
Michelle MacLean, a spokeswoman for the campus. "Limitations for use will be 
discussed, as well as procedures for first aid and decontamination. The 
psychological and physiological effects of these substances on humans will also 
be addressed." 
</P>
<P>
 The program fee is $35. Advance registration is available by calling the 
college's Community Services Office at (714) 891-3991. 
</P>
