<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: NAMES IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brian Keefe, a 6-foot-4, 185-pound shooting guard from Winchester (Mass.) 
High, has signed a financial-aid agreement to play basketball at UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Keefe, the school's all-time leading scorer with 1,163 points, averaged 28 
points a game last season. 
</P>
<P>
 "Brian has good basketball instincts and will be a very good scorer for us," 
Coach Rod Baker said. 
</P>
<P>
 Parry O'Keefe of Laguna Beach defeated John Gabriel of Huntington Beach, 7-5, 
6-1, in the 75 age-group men's singles of the Pacific Southwest Seniors 
Championships at Lindborg Racquet Club in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 In the 65 singles category, Doris Clark of Laguna Beach defeated Santa 
Monica's Do Do Cheney by default. 
</P>
<P>
 Four local surfers advanced to the first round of the main event of the Bud 
Surf Tour at the Lower Trestles in San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Ward and Benji Severson of San Clemente, Branden Faber of Laguna Beach, 
Tim Reardon of Dana Point and Jason Haughey of Laguna Niguel will be competing 
at 7 a.m. today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
