<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CHAPMAN TIES CLAREMONT, 3-3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chapman rallied to tie Claremont, 3-3, in a men's nonconference soccer game 
Wednesday at Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Hurtarte, assisted by his brother, Gary, scored Chapman's second goal at 
the 87-minute mark to tie the score and send it into overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 Claremont's Ryan St. George scored 11 minutes into overtime to take the lead, 
but Ryan Murff of Chapman (2-1-1) tied the score with less than two minutes 
remaining in the final overtime period. Claremont is 3-0-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In women's nonconference soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 2, UC Santa Cruz 1 -- Cindy LeClair scored a goal and assisted on Amy 
Feniello's goal for Chapman (3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Pepperdine 2, UC Irvine 1 -- Anteater Shawna Berke's second-half score came 
too late to catch Pepperdine. Former Orange High standout Debbie Ford scored 
Pepperdine's first goal and Jennifer Evans had the second goal. Stephanie Boes 
had five saves for UC Irvine (2-2). 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego State 3, Cal State Fullerton 2 -- San Diego State's Reese 
Cicchinelli clinched the victory with a goal in the last two minutes. Amber 
Thompson and Jennifer Patterson, with assists from Erin Rico and Debbie Klein, 
scored for the Titans. Cal State Fullerton is 1-3. 
</P>
<P>
 In women's nonconference volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia 3, Redlands 2 -- Amy Bonacorsi led Concordia (8-3) with 17 kills in 
its 12-15, 15-8, 15-1, 7-15, 15-6 victory. Teammate Elani Collais added 15. 
Redlands is 3-4. 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 3, Claremont 0 -- Simone Burgesmeir had 13 kills 
to lead the Vanguards in its victory over Claremont, 15-8, 15-10, 15-9. SCC 
improves to 9-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
