<HEADLINE>
<P>
FASHION / SCREEN STYLE: THE YOUNG AND THE SUITLESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETTY GOODWIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Series: "Extra -- The Entertainment Magazine" (NBC, Monday through Friday, 
7 p.m.). 
</P>
<P>
 The Setup: Hosts Arthel Neville and Dave Nemeth (pictured) introduce segments 
on late-breaking celebrity, movie, television and music news. 
</P>
<P>
 The Look: Neville and Nemeth are in no way living on the same planet as their 
"Entertainment Tonight" rivals, Mary Hart -- in her trademark clothes that 
sparkle -- and John Tesh, in jacket and tie. And yet while always put together, 
Neville and Nemeth don't always come across like they exist in the land of 
reality. Neville, the more polished of the two, fares better than Nemeth, who 
strains to look Hollywood. There's no denying that everything they wear is the 
newest and the latest, but it's not always divine. 
</P>
<P>
 We Could Live Without: Yes, we all know that men wearing shirts buttoned to 
the top and without a tie can be very cool, but certainly not night after 
night. More to the point -- and this may seem horribly old-fashioned -- on a 
slick show such as this, a tie would prove more commanding. Yes, Nemeth's 
unmatching vests and blazers and trousers all worn together can be very 
sophisticated. Seen on television, however, it just looks like he's a man in 
need of a suit. 
</P>
<P>
 On the very night Hart wore one of her metallic-edged suits and camisoles 
(don't forget the rhinestone earrings), Neville -- who strictly wears trousers 
-- donned comparatively subdued gray slacks, satiny patchwork vest and satin 
blouse, which one couldn't help but notice was buttoned to the top exactly like 
that of her co-host. She looks best on nights when she's not working to be In 
Fashion with those novelty shirts, "Extra"-wide trousers and "Extra"-long 
jacket. 
</P>
<P>
 Quoted: "I don't even know where Mary (Hart) gets those kinds of clothes 
anymore, but Arthel wouldn't be caught dead in any of those things. She's just 
a natural woman. The other thing is, Arthel and Dave are about 15 years younger 
than Mary and John," says Cynthia Riley, consulting executive producer, 
explaining why Neville and Nemeth should look different from "Entertainment 
Tonight's" hosts. 
</P>
<P>
 Good Hair Day: The powers-that-be were right in persuading Neville to chop off 
her medium-length hair in favor of a jaunty, short do. How much persuading did 
it take? Riley says Neville was given four hair stylists to interview and short 
wigs to sample. 
</P>
<P>
 Miss: Compared to the polished-looking hosts, the correspondents are a scruffy 
bunch, with Ethan Hawke wanna-be John Norris reporting one day in backward 
baseball cap and sunglasses. 
</P>
<P>
 Sources: The Beverly Hills outpost of Barneys New York provides the hosts' 
wardrobes. BETTY GOODWIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
