<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; VIRGINIA; WILDER REPORTEDLY WILL END SENATE BID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Independent candidate L. Douglas Wilder, trailing badly in new polls, is set 
to announce his withdrawal from the U.S. Senate race in Virginia, a source 
close to the candidate said.Wilder had abruptly left the campaign trail and 
returned to Richmond. His aides said the campaign would have a statement today. 
In deciding to drop out, Wilder cited polls and his inability to raise the 
money necessary to compete against incumbent Democrat Charles S. Robb and 
