<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SURGEON SHOT ON FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 38-year-old orthopedic surgeon was shot in the chest and left wrist 
Wednesday morning as he drove along Interstate 805. 
</P>
<P>
 William Shoemaker, who has offices in Chula Vista, Santee and San Diego, was 
listed in good condition at Mercy Hospital after undergoing surgery.Police have 
no suspects and no motive for the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 A police spokesman said Shoemaker was shot through the windshield of his BMW 
as he drove south on I-805. Shoemaker was talking to his office on his cellular 
phone when he was struck. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses reported hearing popping sounds and seeing a pickup truck that had 
been driving ahead of Shoemaker suddenly pull to the right and get off the 
freeway. The truck was found near a neighborhood bar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
