WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; DESIGN PANEL DECIDES RINK SITE IS UNSAFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A proposed site for Ventura's first outdoor skating rink for in-line hockey 
leagues is too close to the Ventura Freeway, the city's design review committee 
said this week. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee, which met Monday afternoon, is an advisory board only.Would-be 
builders of the rink on Arundell Avenue said they plan to appeal the decision 
to Ventura's Planning Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm very disappointed," said Nicole Soroka, owner of Street Shark's In-Line 
Hockey League and In-Line Hockey Shop on Main Street. "My ultimate concern is 
safety." 
</P>
<P>
 Soroka and her in-line hockey-playing husband, Steve, decided to build the 
rink because their league has grown too large to fit into the busy schedule at 
an indoor rink in Oxnard, where they now play. 
</P>
<P>
 Nicole Soroka said they wanted to install a $100,000, partly prefabricated, 
180-by-80-foot rink. But members of the city committee worried about hazards 
from cars crashing off the highway and onto the facility. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
