WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; MAN ENTERS PLEA IN SHOOTING OF BOY, 13 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Ventura man accused of shooting a 13-year-old boy, who was left paralyzed, 
pleaded not guilty in Ventura County Superior Court on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 After accepting the plea, Superior Court Judge Charles R. McGrath ordered the 
defendant, 21-year-old Brian Adams, to undergo a psychiatric examination as 
requested by the defense. 
</P>
<P>
 Adams' attorney, George C. Eskin, said a doctor could help determine whether 
Adams should change his plea to not guilty by reason of insanity. 
</P>
<P>
 McGrath set Adams' trial for Nov. 7. DWAYNE BRAY 
