<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; JUMBO JET 
LANDS SAFELY AFTER BLOWING 2 TIRES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Thai International Airways jumbo jet that had blown out two of its 18 tires 
on takeoff circled back to Los Angeles International Airport and landed safely 
about 4:30 p.m. Wednesday, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Airport officials said that before returning to LAX, the Boeing 747-400 -- 
which had been bound for Seoul and Bangkok with 390 passengers and crew -- 
circled for about half an hour over the ocean to dump fuel in order to lighten 
the plane's load and reduce pressure on the tires. 
</P>
<P>
 However, they added, the problem was not serious because the damaged tires 
were not part of the jet's nose gear. Passengers on Flight 771 said later that 
many aboard were unaware that a problem had occurred until the plane turned 
back to LAX. 
</P>
</TEXT>
