<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: FLU SHOTS POSTPONED AT COUNTY CLINICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County residents hoping to get an early flu shot from public clinics 
will have to turn to private doctors or wait until November, county health 
officials say. 
</P>
<P>
 Manufacturers delayed the statewide release of the shots, which were due to 
arrive at county clinics this month, the Ventura County Public Health 
Department announced Tuesday.No explanation for the delay was offered. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior citizens, young people and adults with chronic health problems are 
encouraged to be vaccinated to avoid serious health problems associated with 
the flu. 
</P>
<P>
 People on Medicare or MediCal can go to a private doctor to receive flu 
vaccine, county health officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Public Health Department has tentatively rescheduled flu clinics for 
November. More information on the clinics will be available later this month, 
officials said. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</TEXT>
