<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN CRITICALLY HURT, DRIVER HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Reseda woman was arrested on suspicion of hit-and-run driving after an 
accident Wednesday in which a Canoga Park woman was critically injured, Los 
Angeles police reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Ana Mercedes Villanueva, 35, of Canoga Park was listed in critical condition 
at Northridge Hospital Medical Center with head and facial injuries, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Villanueva was driving north on Winnetka Avenue when a vehicle driven by 
Consuelo Morales, 37, of Reseda collided with Villanueva's car as Morales made 
a left turn, police said. Villanueva's car spun out of control and smashed into 
a traffic signal at Winnetka Avenue and Roscoe Boulevard, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Morales fled in her car but was later arrested at her brother's house nearby, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Patrol officers happened to be in the area when they saw her vehicle drive 
up," said Los Angeles Police Sgt. Ben Lee. "As soon as she saw them, she ran 
inside the house, where she was arrested." 
</P>
<P>
 Morales, booked on suspicion of felony hit-and-run driving, was being held in 
lieu of $200,000 bail, police said. 
</P>
