<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: PRO BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dwane Casey, a central figure in Kentucky's 1989 basketball scandal, was named 
an assistant coach with the Seattle SuperSonics. He replaces Bob Kloppenburg, 
who becomes vice president of personnel and scouting. 
</P>
<P>
 The SuperSonics also announced the hiring of Rick Sund, former Dallas Maverick 
vice president, as a consultant to General Manager Wally Walker. 
</P>
<P>
 At Kentucky, Casey was linked to a recruiting scandal when he was an assistant 
under then-Coach Eddie Sutton. Casey's name was on the return address of a 
package sent to the father of Los Angeles Fairfax High star Chris Mills. 
Employees of the air-freight company said the package broke open, revealing 
$1,000. The NCAA concluded that the school had sent the package. Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 The San Diego Padres have signed the Memphis Chicks of the Southern League as 
their double-A affiliate for 1995 and '96. 
</P>
<P>
 Shortstop Derek Jeter, who began the season in Class A and climbed to triple-A 
in the New York Yankee organization, was named Baseball America's minor league 
player of the year. . . . The British lightweight four without coxswain that in 
June posted the fastest 2,000-meter time in history failed to make the final at 
the World Rowing Championships in Indianapolis. 
</P>
