<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LITTLE BIT OF HISTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hart High's two Southern Section championship football teams had common bonds. 
</P>
<P>
 Tom Bonds was the quarterback of the Indians' 1983 Coastal Conference 
championship team. His brother, Jim Bonds, was the quarterback of Hart's 1986 
Northwestern Conference champion. The school retired the No. 7 jersey both wore 
for the Indians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Prep Sports 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA091594-0247 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 079386 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
September 15, 1994, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 7; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
396 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: CON-WAY WESTERN NAMES QUALITY CHIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Julie Gruber has been promoted to director of quality assurance for Con-Way 
Western Express, a Buena Park trucking company. Gruber joined the company in 
1986 as a customer service representative. 
</P>
<P>
 * Michael J. Quinn has been appointed executive vice president, sales and 
marketing for Bergen Brunswig Corp., an Orange-based distributor of 
pharmaceuticals. He was previously president and chief executive of OCP 
America, and before that was president and chief operating officer of the 
Cardinal Health Group subsidiary of Cardinal Distribution Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 * Julien Carralero has been appointed director of food and beverage for the 
Ritz-Carlton hotel in Dana Point. He will be responsible for the daily 
operation of the hotel's restaurants and lounges, as well as the room service, 
banquet and steward departments. Carralero, who has been with the Ritz-Carlton 
Hotel Co. for more than six years, was most recently the director of food and 
beverage at the Ritz-Carlton, Mauna Lani, Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
 * Lawrence A. Scott has joined Lincoln Property Co. in Irvine as director of 
business development. He will head the expansion of the company's third-party 
property management portfolio and assist in property acquisition activities. 
Scott was previously vice president/senior asset manager at American Real 
Estate Group, a subsidiary of American Savings Bank.  
</P>
<P>
 * Rodney A. Wycoff Jr. has joined Strategic Mortgage Services in Costa Mesa as 
director of national policy and programs for the appraisal division. Prior to 
joining the company, Wycoff owned and operated his own appraisal firm, and 
before that was vice president at Equitable Real Estate.  
</P>
<P>
 * Sharon Kielty has been promoted to national sales manager of Acculogic and 
Computer Peripherals Inc., two companies which operate as the ACC Technology 
Group in Irvine. She had been the Western region manager of Acculogic for the 
past two years. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dan Aminoff, vice president and Southern California correspondent division 
manager for Arcs Mortgage Inc., has assumed the additional responsibility of 
overseeing all Orange County wholesale business out of the firm's San Juan 
Capistrano office. Aminoff began his career with Arcs in 1982 and has worked as 
a loan officer for both single-family and multifamily properties as well as a 
retail branch manager in Tustin. Arcs is the mortgage banking affiliate of the 
Bank of New York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
