<P>
BRIEFLY: TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Foreign Share of Japan's Chip Market Rises: Foreign computer chip makers 
grabbed a record 21.9% of Japan's market in the second quarter, the office of 
the U.S. trade representative said, surpassing the level set in a controversial 
U.S.-Japan microchip trade pact. This marked the third straight quarter that 
the foreign share of Japan's semiconductor market topped the critical 20% mark 
under the trade deal. The rise compares to a 20.7% share in the first quarter. 
</P>
