<TEXT>
<P>
 Japan's Overall Trade Surplus Narrows: The Japanese Finance Ministry's report 
for August says the shrinkage was the biggest in four years, but the ministry 
said it is too soon to tell if a trend is developing. The value of exports in 
excess of imports, measured before seasonal adjustment, dropped 19% last month 
to the equivalent of $6.08 billion, from $7.49 billion in August, 1993, the 
ministry said. 
</P>
