<P>
 Winemaker Angelo Papagni, who pled guilty two years ago to falsely selling 
Barbera Grapes as Zinfandel and was sentenced to 18 months in federal prison, 
has had his prison term reduced by three months, making him eligible for 
release this week. Los Angeles attorney David Katz appealed to U.S. District 
