<P>
O.C. OFFICIAL NAMED NEW SCHOOL SUPT. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF KASS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One day before the school year began for the 8,600 students of the Palos 
Verdes Peninsula Unified School District, Ann N. Chlebicki, 44, was named 
superintendent. 
</P>
<P>
 Chlebicki will earn $104,000 a year under a three-year contract unanimously 
approved by the school board Sept. 7.The contract begins Oct. 10. 
</P>
<P>
 Chlebicki was assistant superintendent of instructional services for the 
28,000-student Saddleback Valley Unified School District in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 "When I was checking (Chlebicki's) references, just about everybody was very 
negative -- about the prospect of losing her," said board member Barry J. 
Hildebrand, a trustee. 
</P>
<P>
 She said she will continue to live in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Chlebicki's appointment ends a search begun in April after Michael W. Caston 
left to become superintendent in Santa Barbara. JEFF KASS 
</P>
