<P>
DUARTE CHAMBER PICKS NEW LEADER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Duarte Chamber of Commerce board has appointed a former Paramount 
newspaper editor, who managed the Downey and Bellflower chambers, as its 
executive director. 
</P>
<P>
 David L. Ryal, who is also an ordained minister in the Church of Christ, will 
take over the top seat at the chamber. 
</P>
<P>
 In recent years, some chamber executives have created controversy by publicly 
criticizing City Council actions. The council, in turn, cut funding for the 
chamber. 
</P>
<P>
 For the last 16 months, Ryal has operated his own business and marketing 
consulting firm. 
