<HEADLINE>
<P>
TICKETS GOING FAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEONARD REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tomorrow's opening of "Man of La Mancha" in the 350-seat Forum Theater is 
nearly sold out. Sales for subsequent performances -- on the Friday, Saturday 
and Sunday of each weekend through Oct. 29 -- are brisk. 
</P>
<P>
 Roughly 20 seats remain for single-ticket sales for each of the shows, with 
slightly fewer available on opening night and Saturday night performances, 
according to box office reports. Season ticket subscriptions, are beyond sales 
projections as well. 
</P>
<P>
 For single tickets, call Santa Susana Repertory at 374-8282; for season 
tickets, call 449-ARTS. 
</P>
<P>
 Note: Santa Susana also will present "The Boys in Autumn" in February -- for 
single ticket sales only. 
</P>
<P>
 Opening night and Saturday night will feature modest receptions to which 
ticket holders are welcome. 
</P>
<P>
 But the main opening ceremonies of the Civic Arts Plaza will be reserved until 
the main stage opens with Bernadette Peters the weekend of Oct. 21. LEONARD 
REED 
</P>
</TEXT>
