<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PASADENA; COURT REVOKES ORDER AGAINST COUNCILMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The state Court of Appeal has invalidated a restraining order that prevented 
Councilman Isaac Richard from approaching or telephoning fellow Councilman 
Chris Holden except on official business. 
</P>
<P>
 The three-judge panel found that a Superior Court judge erred last October in 
granting the injunction against Richard based on one incident; Richard yelled 
at and threatened Holden the month before during a UCLA football game at the 
Rose Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 The Court of Appeal found last week that the one incident did not constitute a 
pattern of harassment that warranted a restraining order. 
</P>
</TEXT>
