<LENGTH>
<P>
116 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Debora Vrana Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Home Sales Ranking: Orange County was the nation's No. 4 market for home sales 
in master-planned communities last year, according to a study from the 
accounting firm Arthur Andersen. 
</P>
<P>
 A total of 48 master-planned communities with more than 2,500 acres were 
tracked in the study. Sales of new housing units totaled 19,077 for 1993. 
Combined residential home sales at four master-planned communities in Orange 
County -- Rancho Santa Margarita, Aliso Viejo, Mission Viejo and Irvine -- came 
to 2,044 units, or 11% of total nationwide. 
</P>
<P>
 Houston had the largest number of master-planned community home sales in the 
nation, with Las Vegas and Fort Lauderdale, Fla., coming in second and third. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
