<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Debora Vrana Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irvine Co. Project: Villa Coronado, the first building constructed by Irvine 
Co.'s apartment division, is underway off Harvard Avenue in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 KTGY Group, an Irvine architect, is designing clusters of three-story 
Venetian-style buildings to house the 513 Villa Coronado apartments, which 
range in size from 700 square feet to 1,108 square feet. 
</P>
<P>
 The firm is also designing two other apartment projects for Irvine Apartment 
Communities. They are Rancho Monterey, a 436-unit complex in Tustin featuring a 
Monterey architectural style, and Santa Rosa, a 368-unit Mediterranean-style 
complex in Irvine. Both will be completed next year. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Coronado is the first project by Irvine Apartment Communities Inc., a 
real estate investment trust created by Irvine Co. in a public stock offering 
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
