<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. EARNINGS: ADMAR'S PROFIT DECREASES BY 5% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Admar Group Inc., a Santa Ana managed health care services company, reported a 
profit of $126,000, or 1 cent a share, for the second fiscal quarter, down 5% 
from the $132,000, or 2 cents a share, recorded for the comparable quarter of 
1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenue for the quarter ended July 31 declined to $4.3 million from $4.6 
million. Profit for the first half increased to $293,000, or 3 cents a share, 
from $281,000, or 3 cents a share, for the same period last year. Revenue 
dropped 7%, to $8.6 million from $9.2 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
