<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: FIRST AMERICAN BUYS TITLE INSURER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 First American Financial Corp., the nation's second-largest title insurer, 
said Wednesday that it has purchased Eureka Title Co. in Humboldt County from 
the family of the late founder, E.G. Wilkenloh. 
</P>
<P>
 Terms of the deal were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 Eureka Title had been First American's exclusive agent in its area since the 
start of the year. Current management and employees will continue with the 
operation under First American, said Parker S. Kennedy, First American's 
president. 
</P>
<P>
 The transaction is the sixth acquisition for the Santa Ana company this year 
and continues its long pursuit of title insurers and agencies as part of its 
growth strategy. In separate deals, it previously acquired firms in Florida, 
North Carolina, Texas, Wyoming and Washington, D.C. 
</P>
</TEXT>
