<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coram Healthcare Corp.: The company announced the completion of its 
acquisition of HMSS, a Houston-based provider of home health care, for an 
undisclosed sum.Coram purchased HMSS from Secoamerica Inc., a diversified 
holding company. Both Coram and Secoamerica are headquartered in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 HMSS provides intravenous therapy in homes, offices and schools through 20 
offices nationwide. Coram has offices in 18 of the 20 markets in which HMSS 
operate and hopes to consolidate operations in those markets. 
</P>
<P>
 Coram was formed July 8, through of four-way merger of T2 Medical, Curaflex 
Health Services, Medisys Inc. and HealthInfusion Inc. 
</P>
