<HEADLINE>
<P>
BENEFIT BASKETBALL GAME IS SCHEDULED FOR OCT. 1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Tiny "Zeus" Lister Jr. celebrity basketball game is scheduled Oct. 1 at 
Cal State Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 The benefit game organized by Lister, 36, a Compton High graduate and former 
Long Beach City College shotputter, will feature former Laker Magic Johnson, 
Tommy Ford of the television show "Martin" and actor-director Robert Townsend. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds will benefit the Cal State L.A. athletic scholarship fund and the 
West Angeles Church of God in Christ community revitalization project. 
</P>
<P>
 Lister is best known as the professional wrestler Zeus, who challenged Hulk 
Hogan to a wrestling match in the 1989 film "No Holds Barred." 
</P>
<P>
 The 1982 NCAA Division II shotput champion and school record-holder at Cal 
State L.A., Lister was a regular on HBO's "1st & Ten" series and co-starred 
with Mario Van Peebles and Tone Loc in the film "Posse." 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is $15 and $10. Information: (213) 343-5308. 
</P>
